In [[Seneca people|Seneca]] mythology, '''Djieien''' is a monstrous spider six feet tall. It could not be killed because it had hidden its heart underground. The great hero Othegwenhda ([[Hiawatha]]) discovered Dijien's heart and so killed it.<ref>{{cite book |last1=Bane |first1=Theresa |title=Encyclopedia of Beasts and Monsters in Myth, Legend and Folklore |date=2016 |publisher=McFarland |isbn=978-1-4766-2268-2 |page=103 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=7PYWDAAAQBAJ&pg=PA103 |accessdate=Aug 18, 2018}}</ref>
Djieien figures in the tale of ''Hagowanen and Ot'hegwenhda''.<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Curtin |first1=Jeremiah |last2=Hewitt |first2=J.N.B. |title=Seneca Fiction, Legengs, and Myths |journal=Thirty-Second Annual Report of the Bureau of American Ethnology |date=1918 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=_vQNAAAAIAAJ| page=376 |accessdate=Aug 18, 2018}}</ref>
