A '''reversible garment''' is a garment that can be worn two ways. There is no true "[[wikt:inside out|inside out]]" to a reversible garment, since either way, it gives a fashionable appearance.<ref name="google">{{cite book|title=Webster's II New College Dictionary|author1=Houghton Mifflin Company|author2=Webster|date=1999|publisher=Houghton Mifflin Company|isbn=9780395962145|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=vsaXzwMndS8C|page=949|accessdate=2015-04-05}}</ref> Garments that are commonly made reversible include [[hat]]s, [[jacket]]s, [[vest]]s, [[sweater]]s, [[shirt]]s, [[trousers]], and [[skirt]]s.<ref name="freepatentsonline">{{cite web|url=http://www.freepatentsonline.com/7441281.html|title=Multi reversible garment - Salem, Tamara|publisher=freepatentsonline.com|accessdate=2015-04-05}}</ref><ref name="nytimes">{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1991/08/03/business/patents-mix-match-mix-match-keep-going.html|title=Patents - Mix, Match. Mix, Match. Keep Going. - NYTimes.com|publisher=nytimes.com|accessdate=2015-04-05}}</ref>

Reversible garments have some features unlike other types of garments, such as thicker overall fabric (since two fabric are often sewn together), [[button]]s on both sides (in garments that have buttons), different types of stitching, and no tags.<ref name="google2">{{cite book|title=The Zapp Method of Couture Sewing: Tailor Garments Easily Using Any Pattern|author=Zapp, A.|date=2004|publisher=Krause Publications|isbn=9780873496810|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=ATMc_oHvPfsC|pages=2–77|accessdate=2015-04-05}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id%3D6gM9qmMOcW8C%26pg%3DPA44%26dq%3D%2522reversible%2Bgarment%2522%26lr%3D%26as_brr%3D3%26ie%3DISO-8859-1%26output%3Dhtml |accessdate=October 18, 2009 }}{{dead link|date=June 2016|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref>

Ancient [[shepherd]]s used to have reversible garments with a warm side that they would wear when the weather was cold, and a cool side when the weather was hot.<ref name="google3">{{cite book|title=Jeremiah: Volume 2: 26-52|author=McKane, W.|date=2000|publisher=Bloomsbury Academic|isbn=9780567097323|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=x--hxEWKUYgC|page=1059|accessdate=2015-04-05}}</ref>

